Package civitas.celestis.util.group

Class ArrayGrid<E>

java.lang.Object
civitas.celestis.util.group.ArrayGrid<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The type of element to store in this grid
All Implemented Interfaces:
Grid<E>, Group<E>, Serializable, Iterable<E>
public class ArrayGrid<E> extends Object implements Grid<E>
A grid which uses a two-dimensional array to store its values.

    • merge

      @Nonnull public ArrayGrid<E> merge(@Nonnull Grid<E> g, @Nonnull BinaryOperator<E> f) throws IllegalArgumentException
      Merges this grid with another grid of the same dimensions. The merger function f is applied to each component, and the resulting grid is returned.

      For example, if a sum function (x, y) -> x + y was provided, this would return the sum of the two grids of numbers. This is just an example, and matrices should be used for arithmetic operations.

      Specified by:
      merge in interface Grid<E>
      Parameters:
      g - The other grid to merge with
      f - The merger function to apply
      Returns:
      The resulting grid
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - When the provided grid g's dimensions do not match to this grid's dimensions
